        "id": 3036507,
        "name": "Perone Michael",
        "username": "Perone_Michael",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/bb73d2/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-11-29T04:23:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My brother has been a fan of wine for a good ten years, and I am looking for a book that I could offer for Christmas. I am looking for something different from the great classics because he already have several. The goal would be to find him something rather French winegrowers because he has a preference for French Rhone wines since he lived there a little.<br>\nI saw on a___zon, 3 books:<br>\n1 Guide to the best wines of France 2020 (French)<br>\n2 Bettane and Desseauve wine guide 2020 (French)<br>\n3 The Great Guide of Fine French Wines: 2021 Annual Report, Wines &amp; Winemarkers Under The Radar (English)</p>\n<p>Ever heard these ?<br>\nDo you have any recommendations?</p>\n<p>Thank you !</p>\n<p>Michael.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T23:51:28.917Z",
