      {
        "id": 3036548,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-11-29T13:30:02.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"166042\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>My brother has been a fan of wine for a good ten years, and I am looking for a book that I could offer for Christmas. I am looking for something different from the great classics because he already have several. The goal would be to find him something rather French winegrowers because he has a preference for French Rhone wines since he lived there a little.<br>\nI saw on a___zon, 3 books:<br>\n1 Guide to the best wines of France 2020 (French)<br>\n2 Bettane and Desseauve wine guide 2020 (French)<br>\n3 The Great Guide of Fine French Wines: 2021 Annual Report, Wines &amp; Winemarkers Under The Radar (English)</p>\n<p>Ever heard these ?<br>\nDo you have any recommendations?</p>\n<p>Thank you !</p>\n<p>Michael.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Number 1 on your list would be the latest edition of the RVF\u2019s guide, which, at least for Burgundy, is (sadly) hard to take very seriously these days; perhaps they\u2019re doing better in the Rh\u00f4ne? But I\u2019d go with Bettane &amp; Desseauve, personally.</p>",
